{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_29","type":"agent_message","text":"{\"reviewer\":\"codex\",\"schemaVersion\":1,\"scores\":null,\"weightedTotal\":null,\"verdict\":\"FAIL\",\"issues\":[{\"severity\":\"P2\",\"location\":\"src/app/space/[id]/page.tsx:75\",\"description\":\"The BANNED-before-role invariant is only applied to the pre-upsert read. In the create path, `upsert` may take the update/collision branch and returns only `{ role }`; if the existing row is or becomes `restriction: \\\"BANNED\\\"` between the initial `findUnique` and the `upsert`, the page assigns `role = upserted.role` and renders `SpaceClient` without rechecking restriction. This leaves a race-shaped variant of the r1 BANNED-admin role leak, and the page tests currently cannot catch it because they mock upsert as returning role only.\",\"recommendation\":\"Change the upsert select to include `restriction`, then re-apply the BANNED guard after upsert before passing role to `SpaceClient` (or make the create/read decision transactional with a postcondition check). Add a page test where initial membership lookup is null but upsert returns an OWNER/STAFF row with `restriction: \\\"BANNED\\\"` and assert redirect.\",\"defer\":false,\"deferRationale\":null,\"fixNow\":true}]}"}}
